CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Election Law – Local Board of Elections Employees – Authority at Polling
3 Places, Early Voting Centers, and Counting Centers – Revisions
4 FOR the purpose of requiring a police officer who is on duty at a polling place to obey the
5 authority of the State Administrator, the Deputy State Administrator, or a local board
6 of elections employee a local election director; providing that local board employees,
7 while serving, in a polling place, have a local election director has certain individuals
8 have the authority to keep the peace and order the arrest of certain persons;
9 authorizing requiring a local board employees election director, while serving in a
10 polling place, to protect certain rights of, certain challengers and watchers;
11 authorizing a local election director, while serving in a polling place, to deny
12 admission of, and eject certain challengers and watchers from a polling place under
13 certain circumstances; altering the persons that may designate a registered voter as
14 an accredited challenger or watcher at each polling place; authorizing certain
15 persons to designate accredited challengers or watchers at early voting centers;
